en: Toledo 1981.110
comparanda

Other vases by the Creusa Painter with two male-female pairs on side B include a fragment of a volute krater in the collection of Dr. H. Jucker, Berne (Trendall 1967, p. 87, no. 426, pl. 40, no. 3, probably a volute krater), and a volute krater in Leningrad (Trendall 1967, p. 88, no. 428, pl. 41, no. 1).
condit

On side A, the woman carrying a kottabos stand had lost part of her right shoulder and a small portion of the hair at the back of her head. In addition, part of a bunch of grapes over Pan's head was restored.
